00:24:51,991 --> 00:24:56,362
WE CAN SEE YOU IN EVERY MALL.
WHY DIDN'T I THINK OF THAT?"
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
BEEN IN BUSINESS?

00:24:56,362 --> 00:24:59,698
ABOUT THREE AND A HALF YEARS.
AND HOW MUCH ARE YOU GROSSING
EACH YEAR?

00:24:59,698 --> 00:25:03,502
UM, EVERY YEAR WE'VE INCREASED
OUR INCOME 100%.

00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:05,537
WHAT WAS IT LAST YEAR?

00:25:05,537 --> 00:25:08,007
WE HAD BASICALLY $13,000.
WE DID HAVE‐‐

00:25:08,007 --> 00:25:10,175
OOH.

00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:12,811
KIMBERLY,
I ADMIRE ANYBODY WHO IS

00:25:12,811 --> 00:25:15,214
PASSIONATE ABOUT WHAT THEY DO.

00:25:15,214 --> 00:25:17,916
BUT IF YOU CAN'T MAKE
ENOUGH MONEY FROM THE STORE

00:25:17,916 --> 00:25:19,551
TO EARN A LIVING,

00:25:19,551 --> 00:25:22,821
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK THAT YOU
COULD SELL THIS AS A FRANCHISE

00:25:22,821 --> 00:25:24,423
TO SOMEBODY ELSE?

00:25:24,423 --> 00:25:27,426
WELL, WHEN WE STARTED OUT
THREE AND A HALF YEARS AGO,

00:25:27,426 --> 00:25:29,962
WE DID‐‐WE FOUND A RETAIL SPACE
WE COULD AFFORD.

00:25:29,962 --> 00:25:33,932
UM, AND WE DO THINK THAT
IN A PRIME RETAIL LOCATION,

00:25:33,932 --> 00:25:36,068
IT COULD DO
NOTHING BUT FLOURISH.

00:25:36,068 --> 00:25:40,539
SO OPENING A SECOND LOCATION
WOULD GIVE US THE EXPERIENCE‐‐

00:25:40,539 --> 00:25:43,509
WAIT A MINUTE. THE FIRST
LOCATION ISN'T MAKING MONEY YET.

00:25:43,509 --> 00:25:45,611
SO HOW LONG

00:25:45,611 --> 00:25:49,281
ARE YOU GOING TO LET THIS RUN
BEFORE IT MAKES A PROFIT?

00:25:49,281 --> 00:25:51,717
GOING INTO THIS,
WE DIDN'T HAVE ANY RETAIL

00:25:51,717 --> 00:25:54,086
OR BUSINESS EXPERIENCE,
AND DOING A LOT OF RESEARCH,

00:25:54,086 --> 00:25:56,588
WE'D ALWAYS BEEN TOLD‐‐
ABOUT THREE TO FIVE YEARS‐‐

00:25:56,588 --> 00:25:59,158
IT'S GONNA BE TOUGH,
AND YOU'RE GOING TO STRUGGLE.

00:25:59,158 --> 00:26:01,693
OKAY, YOU'RE IN YEAR FOUR
COMING UP NOW, RIGHT?

00:26:01,693 --> 00:26:04,329
CORRECT. SO IT IS SOMETHING
WE DO THINK ABOUT.

00:26:04,329 --> 00:26:07,132
HOW MUCH MONEY HAVE YOU PUT IN
FROM THE BEGINNING?

00:26:07,132 --> 00:26:10,035
UM, ABOUT $120,000.

00:26:10,035 --> 00:26:14,006
WHERE DID YOU
GET THAT MONEY FROM?

00:26:14,006 --> 00:26:16,141
UM, HELP FROM, UM, FAMILY.

00:26:16,141 --> 00:26:18,444
FRIENDS, FAMILY, SMALL LOANS.

00:26:18,444 --> 00:26:20,979
WHAT IS YOUR HISTORY,
AND‐‐AND WHY DO I BELIEVE

00:26:20,979 --> 00:26:24,550
THERE'S A PASSION YOU HAVE
IN THIS?
MY MOM AND MY SISTER
ARE BOTH TEACHERS.

00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:26,051
I ADORE CHILDREN.

00:26:26,051 --> 00:26:28,687
(voice breaking)
AND I HAVEN'T FOUND A...

00:26:28,687 --> 00:26:31,390
(whispers) SORRY.

00:26:33,358 --> 00:26:35,928
WHY ARE YOU CRYING, KIMBERLY?

00:26:35,928 --> 00:26:38,764
(crying) I'M NOT SURE,
'CAUSE I AM PASSIONATE ABOUT IT.

00:26:38,764 --> 00:26:41,166
I HAVEN'T FOUND A JOB
THAT I'VE WANTED TO DO

00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:43,202
SINCE THE DAY THIS OPENED.

00:26:45,904 --> 00:26:47,906
I TRULY ENJOY
THE SHOPPERS COMING IN.

00:26:47,906 --> 00:26:51,076
I HAVE A GREAT TIME WITH THEM.
(sniffles)

00:26:51,076 --> 00:26:54,947
AND I THINK IT CAN SUCCEED.

00:26:54,947 --> 00:26:59,017
KIMBERLY, LOOK,
I GET THE‐‐THE PASSION PIECE,

00:26:59,017 --> 00:27:03,021
BUT YOU KNOW
WHAT I'D BE CRYING ABOUT?

00:27:03,021 --> 00:27:05,023
THE FACT
YOU'RE NOT MAKING A PROFIT.

00:27:07,993 --> 00:27:10,896
YOU KNOW, I‐I DON'T LIKE
TO THINK THAT WAY,

00:27:10,896 --> 00:27:14,666
BECAUSE I REALLY BELIEVE
IT CAN. UM...

00:27:14,666 --> 00:27:17,569
KIMBERLY, I'M GONNA ASSUME
50% GROSS MARGINS.

00:27:17,569 --> 00:27:22,608
YOU NEED TO DO $200,000
IN THIS STORE TO BREAK EVEN,

00:27:22,608 --> 00:27:26,745
TO PAY YOURSELF
AND YOUR BROTHER A SALARY.

00:27:26,745 --> 00:27:30,883
MORE, KEVIN. THEY NEED TO DO
FAR MORE THAN THAT.
AT LEAST. I'M SAYING IF YOU
JUST TOOK OUT $30,000 EACH.

00:27:30,883 --> 00:27:33,852
IT'S A HUGE ISSUE. FROM
AN INVESTMENT POINT OF VIEW,

00:27:33,852 --> 00:27:36,388
IT HAS NO MERIT,
BECAUSE YOU HAVEN'T PROVEN‐‐

00:27:36,388 --> 00:27:39,124
BEFORE YOU BUILD
A SECOND STORE‐‐

00:27:39,124 --> 00:27:41,760
THE FIRST ONE MAKES MONEY.

00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:44,463
I LOVE KIDS, BUT THEY'RE
THE HARDEST THINGS TO SELL TO

00:27:44,463 --> 00:27:46,865
'CAUSE THEY DON'T HAVE
THEIR OWN CREDIT CARDS.

00:27:46,865 --> 00:27:49,968
ONCE WE GET THE PARENTS
IN THE STORE,

00:27:49,968 --> 00:27:52,504
THEY'RE HAPPY TO LET
THEIR CHILDREN SPEND MONEY,

00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:55,107
AND THEN THEY'RE PICKING UP
THINGS AS WELL.

00:27:55,107 --> 00:27:57,609
THERE'S NOTHING MORE EVIL
THAN A BUSINESS

00:27:57,609 --> 00:28:01,180
THAT DOESN'T CREATE A PROFIT.

00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:04,283
AND THE ONLY WAY TO FIGHT EVIL
IS WITH EVIL.

00:28:04,283 --> 00:28:07,319
YOU HAVE TO SHUT IT DOWN.

00:28:07,319 --> 00:28:09,354
I'M SORRY. IT'S THE TRUTH.

00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:11,657
AND FOR THAT REASON,
I'M OUT.

00:28:14,393 --> 00:28:16,995
YOU STILL LEAVE
AT THE END OF A YEAR

00:28:16,995 --> 00:28:19,998
WITH $13,000, NO SALARY.

00:28:19,998 --> 00:28:22,768
YOU OWE YOUR RELATIVES MONEY.

00:28:22,768 --> 00:28:27,072
I JUST FEEL LIKE THIS IS
A HOBBY THAT YOU LOVE.

00:28:27,072 --> 00:28:29,942
BUT BY NO MEANS
IS IT A BUSINESS.

00:28:29,942 --> 00:28:33,845
I AM DEFINITELY, UH, OUT.

00:28:37,282 --> 00:28:40,118
KEVIN, I‐I DISAGREE THAT SHE
SHOULD SHUT THE BUSINESS DOWN.

00:28:40,118 --> 00:28:42,688
I THINK YOU'VE GROWN
THE BUSINESS, CORRECT?

00:28:42,688 --> 00:28:44,823
100% EVERY YEAR.
YES.

00:28:44,823 --> 00:28:47,960
SO TAKE‐‐TAKE THE NEXT YEAR.
DON'T GO FRANCHISE THE BUSINESS.

00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:51,463
I'D BRING MY SON THERE TO SHOP,
AND HE'D PROBABLY LOVE IT,

00:28:51,463 --> 00:28:54,733
BUT AS AN INVESTMENT, IT‐‐IT
WOULDN'T BE FOR ME, SO I'M OUT.

00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:57,536
SHAME ON YOU
FOR ENCOURAGING HER.

00:28:57,536 --> 00:29:00,038
WELL, AT THIS POINT,
YOU'RE FAILING.

00:29:00,038 --> 00:29:03,742
BUT FAILURE, TO ME,
IS JUST AN OPPORTUNITY

00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:06,878
TO BEGIN AGAIN MORE WISELY.

00:29:06,878 --> 00:29:09,748
I REGRET TO SAY IT‐‐
I'M OUT.

00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:16,088
IT'S AN ADMIRABLE IDEA,

00:29:16,088 --> 00:29:19,324
BUT PART OF WHAT KEVIN SAYS
IS‐‐IS RIGHT.

00:29:19,324 --> 00:29:22,127
ALL OF WHAT HE SAYS
IS RIGHT. 100%.
BUT...

00:29:22,127 --> 00:29:24,196
NO, 122%.

00:29:24,196 --> 00:29:28,433
IT'S HARD TO CALL SOMETHING
GEARED TO CHILDREN EVIL. UH‐‐

00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:31,403
THE <i>BUSINESS</i> IS EVIL.

00:29:31,403 --> 00:29:32,838
BUT, REALLY,

00:29:32,838 --> 00:29:35,240
THERE ISN'T ANY DATA

00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:39,244
THAT SUPPORTS EXPANDING
THIS BUSINESS TODAY.

00:29:39,244 --> 00:29:41,113
I'M OUT.

00:29:43,215 --> 00:29:47,185
KIMBERLY, I'M YOUR ONLY FRIEND
UP HERE.

00:29:47,185 --> 00:29:49,554
I'M THE ONLY ONE
TELLING YOU THE TRUTH.

00:29:49,554 --> 00:29:52,057
ALL THIS ENCOURAGEMENT
FOR YOU TO GO ON IS FOLLY.

00:29:52,057 --> 00:29:53,859
IT'S A HUGE MISTAKE.

00:29:53,859 --> 00:29:56,728
SOMEBODY'S GOTTA TELL YOU THAT.
IT'S NOT GONNA BE YOUR FAMILY.

00:29:56,728 --> 00:29:58,964
IT'S NOT GONNA BE
THESE PEOPLE CHEERING YOU ON.

00:29:58,964 --> 00:30:01,266
IT'S ME.
I DON'T THINK I‐‐I DON'T
THINK WE'RE CHEERING HER ON.

00:30:01,266 --> 00:30:03,302
I THINK THAT‐‐
I DON'T CARE, ROBERT.
IT MAKES NO MONEY.

00:30:03,302 --> 00:30:05,871
I THINK THE ONLY MISTAKE
THAT KIMBERLY'S MAKING

00:30:05,871 --> 00:30:09,107
IS THAT THE DATA IS TELLING HER
TO PERHAPS CHANGE DIRECTION.

00:30:09,107 --> 00:30:12,010
IS THAT ANOTHER WAY OF SAYING,
"SHUT IT DOWN?"

00:30:13,912 --> 00:30:17,182
AT THE VERY LEAST,
GO HOME TONIGHT,

00:30:17,182 --> 00:30:19,751
WRITE ON A PIECE OF PAPER

00:30:19,751 --> 00:30:21,753
THE DATE THAT YOU
HAVE TO BE PROFITABLE,

00:30:21,753 --> 00:30:24,022
AND BE HONEST WITH YOURSELF.

00:30:24,022 --> 00:30:26,858
YOU HAVE GOT TO
PUT A TIMELINE ON THIS

00:30:26,858 --> 00:30:29,661
BECAUSE IT'S YOUR FAMILY'S MONEY
YOU'RE BURNING,

00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:32,831
AND THAT I FIND EVIL.
I APPRECIATE
ALL OF YOUR, UM, OPINIONS,

00:30:32,831 --> 00:30:36,201
AND WE APPRECIATE YOUR TIME.
(Daymond) GOOD LUCK.

00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:40,305
I MEAN, SHE WAS
REALLY PASSIONATE.

00:30:40,305 --> 00:30:44,309
